# {{ repo_name }} — autonomous research

This is an experiment to have an LLM conduct its own research toward the
following purpose, with an idea priority queue ensuring every experiment tried
is a well-thought-out, reasonable one.

## Purpose
{{ purpose }}

## Setup
1. **Agree on a run tag** — propose one based on today's date (e.g. `mar5`).
   The branch `autoresearch/<tag>` must not already exist.
2. **Create the branch:** `git checkout -b autoresearch/<tag>` from master.
3. **Read the in-scope files:** `README.md`, `prepare.py` (fixed: data prep +
   evaluation — do not modify), `train.py` (the file you modify), `ideas.md`.
4. **Verify data exists**; if not, run `uv run prepare.py`.
5. **Initialize `results.tsv`** with just the header row.
6. **Fill in `ideas.md`** — research each seed idea, think hard, and expand each
   into a full idea block.
7. **Ensure `arui` is configured** — every run logs via the `arui` SDK.
8. **Confirm and go.**

## The idea-block format
Each idea in `ideas.md`:

    #
    - idea_id: `<run name used for arui / results.tsv>`
    - Description: `<plain-language description, math, citations, prior data>`
    - EV Improvement: `<confidence 0-1  ×  expected metric gain>`
    - Why: `<reason this idea will work>`
    - Time of idea generation: `<timestamp>`
    - Status: `<not_implemented | implemented | running | failed | success | unclear>`
    - HPPs: `<all hyperparameters/configs used, after the run starts>`
    - Time of run start and end: `<start> - <end>`
    - Results vs. Baseline: `<e.g. 0.531 at5_acc vs 0.412 baseline, +0.119>`
    - arui link: `<link to the run's dashboard report>`
    - Analysis: `<deep analysis of what happened>`
    - Conclusion: `<final verdict>`
    - Next Ideas to Try: `<spawned ideas — add new idea blocks>`
    #

## Experimentation
- The evaluation metric is **{{ validation_metric }}** ({{ metric_direction }}).
- Each run has a fixed wall-clock time budget defined here.
- You may modify `train.py` freely; you may NOT modify `prepare.py` or the
  evaluation harness, and you may NOT add dependencies.
- Keep all {{ gpu_count }} GPU(s) busy at all times — no wasteful runs.

## The experiment loop (run forever)
1. Review `ideas.md`; pick the highest-EV unstarted idea.
2. Implement it by editing `train.py`; commit.
3. Run it on a free GPU; log via `arui`.
4. Read results; if the metric improved, keep the commit, else revert.
5. Log to `results.tsv`; write Analysis / Conclusion / Next Ideas into the
   idea block; append any new idea blocks.
6. Go to 1. Never stop on your own.
